long_description:
Thinking of brushing up on your skills and attending a tech event in the nation’s tech capital? San Francisco and Silicon Valley are the epicenter of the tech world, and with this comes some of the most relevant tech conventions available today. 

If you're looking for a place to stay while in SF, check out our tech-forward boutique hotel in Nob Hill. Stanford Court Hotel boasts progressive tech and eco-friendly amenities that reflect the forward-thinking culture of SF. Make sure to check out our newly-rebooted rooms and offers.

Without further ado, take a look at upcoming tech events in San Francisco for the last half of 2018.

BoxWorks

When - Aug. 29-30, 2018

Where - Moscone Center, 747 Howard St., San Francisco

Why you should go - This is a must for the digital-first company. Hear from forward thinking leaders like Netflix, Microsoft, Slack and NASA. Breakout sessions abound at BoxWorks, as well as training sessions and keynotes. BoxWorks is all about making the best possible use of available technology in order to launch new ideas. 

TechCrunch Disrupt SF 2018

When - Sept. 5-7, 2018

Where - Moscone Center, 747 Howard St., San Francisco

Why you should go - The tech game is always changing, and those at TechCrunch.com are always ahead of the curve. This event for startups, hackers, investors and tech-leaders, focusing on artificial intelligence and machine learning in the real world. Take advantage of talktime and a Q&A by former president of Google China Kai-Fu Lee, current CEO and chairman of Sinovation, and predictor of all things technology and artificial intelligence). Get your tickets today, before the event sells out!

 

Dreamforce

When - Sept. 25-28, 2018

Where - Multiple venues across San Francisco. See list.

Why you should go - This annual user conference is all about dreaming big, getting inspired, and going for it. This year’s speakers include Al Gore, will.i.am, Bloomberg’s Emily Chang and more. It should be nothing short of inspirational. Over 2,700 breakout sessions, training, hands-on demos and certification opportunities are planned for the four-day, trailblazing event. Check out your registration options.

GitHub Universe

When - Oct. 16-17, 2018

Where - Palace of Fine Arts, 3301 Lyon St., San Francisco

Why you should go - Learn the best practices in the software community with GitHub’s flagship event, Universe. This is the best way to sharpen your tool kit and keep up-to-date with software trends and solutions, covering two days of exchange with leading experts in the field. Tickets almost always sell out for the event, so make sure to register ahead of time. 

Oracle OpenWorld

When - Oct. 22-25, 2018

Where - Moscone Center, 747 Howard St., San Francisco

Why you should go - Hands-on experience and labs make Oracle’s OpenWorld one of lasting impressions in the world of tech conventions. Grow your business or skill with the influence of exhibitions, demos, labs and one-on-one conversations with fellow experts that explore the art of leading cloud technologies. Register here.

--

 

Stanford Court is a boutique hotel located in Nob Hill. Close to Chinatown, Union Square, and North Beach, Stanford Court Hotel offers free bike rentals to make every part of San Francisco accessible to our guests.
